<inglise> DIRECTIVE 1999/95/EC OF THE EUROPEAN PARLIAMENT AND OF THE COUNCIL of 13 December 1999 concerning the enforcement of provisions in respect of seafarers' hours of work on board ships calling at Community ports </inglise>
<eesti> EUROOPA PARLAMENDI JA N&Otilde;UKOGU DIREKTIIV 1999/95/E&Uuml;, milles k&auml;sitletakse meremeeste t&ouml;&ouml;aega reguleerivate s&auml;tete t&auml;itmist &uuml;henduse sadamates peatuvatel laevadel 13. detsember 1999 </eesti>
<inglise> THE EUROPEAN PARLIAMENT AND THE COUNCIL OF THE EUROPEAN UNION, </inglise>
<eesti> EUROOPA PARLAMENT JA EUROOPA LIIDU N&Otilde;UKOGU, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Community, and in particular Article 80(2) thereof, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa &Uuml;henduse asutamislepingut, eriti selle artikli 80 l&otilde;iget 2, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the proposal from the Commission(1), </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse komisjoni ettepanekut, (1) </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the opinion of the Economic and Social Committee(2), </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse majandus- ja sotsiaalkomitee arvamust, (2) </eesti>
<inglise> Acting in accordance with the procedure laid down in Article 251 of the Treaty(3), </inglise>
<eesti> tegutsedes asutamislepingu artiklis 251 s&auml;testatud menetluste kohaselt (3) </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas: </inglise>
<eesti> ning arvestades, et: </eesti>
<inglise> (1) Community action in the field of social policy aims, inter alia, at improving the health and safety of workers in their working environment; </inglise>
<eesti> 1) sotsiaalpoliitika valdkonnas on &uuml;henduse tegevuse eesm&auml;rk muu hulgas parandada t&ouml;&ouml;tajate tervist ja ohutust nende t&ouml;&ouml;keskkonnas; </eesti>
<inglise> (2) Community action in the field of maritime transport aims, inter alia, at improving shipboard living and working conditions of seafarers, safety at sea and the prevention of pollution caused by maritime accidents; </inglise>
<eesti> 2) meretranspordi valdkonnas on &uuml;henduse tegevuse eesm&auml;rk muu hulgas parandada meremeeste elu- ja t&ouml;&ouml;tingimusi laevadel ja meres&otilde;iduohutust ning &auml;ra hoida laeva&otilde;nnetuste tagaj&auml;rjel tekkivat saastet; </eesti>
<inglise> (3) During its eighty-fourth session of 8 to 22 October 1996 the International Labour Organisation Conference (ILO) adopted ILO Convention No 180 concerning Seafarers' Hours of Work and the Manning of Ships, 1996 (hereinafter "ILO Convention No 180" and the Protocol to the Merchant Shipping (Minimum Standards) Convention, 1976 (hereinafter "the Protocol to ILO Convention No 147"); </inglise>
<eesti> 3) Rahvusvaheline T&ouml;&ouml;organisatsioon (ILO) v&otilde;ttis oma 84. istungj&auml;rgul 8.-22. oktoobrini 1996 vastu ILO 1996. aasta meremeeste t&ouml;&ouml;aja ja laevade mehitamise konventsiooni nr 180 (edaspidi "ILO konventsioon nr 180") ja 1976. aasta kaubandusliku meres&otilde;idu (miinimumnormide) konventsiooni 1996. aasta protokolli (edaspidi "ILO konventsiooni nr 147 protokoll"); </eesti>
<inglise> (4) Council Directive 99/63/EC of 21 June 1999 concerning the Agreement on the organisation of working time of seafarers concluded by the European Community Shipowners' Association (ECSA) and the Federation of Transport Workers' Unions in the European Union (FST) (4) adopted under Article 139(2) of the Treaty, aims to put into effect the said Agreement concluded on 30 September 1998 (hereinafter the "Agreement"); the content of the Agreement reflects certain provisions of ILO Convention No 180; the Agreement applies to seafarers on board every seagoing ship, whether publicly or privately owned, which is registered in the territory of any Member State and is ordinarily engaged in commercial maritime operations; </inglise>
<eesti> 4) asutamislepingu artikli 139 l&otilde;ike 2 kohaselt vastuv&otilde;etud n&otilde;ukogu 21. juuni 1999. aasta direktiivi 99/63/E&Uuml;, milles k&auml;sitletakse Euroopa &Uuml;henduse Reederite &Uuml;hingu (ECSA) ja Euroopa Liidu Transpordit&ouml;&ouml;liste Ameti&uuml;hingute Liidu (FST) s&otilde;lmitud kokkulepet meremeeste t&ouml;&ouml;aja korralduse kohta, (4) eesm&auml;rk on k&otilde;nealune 30. septembril 1998 s&otilde;lmitud kokkulepe (edaspidi "kokkulepe") j&otilde;ustada; k&otilde;nealuses kokkuleppes kajastatakse ILO konventsiooni nr 180 teatavaid s&auml;tteid; k&otilde;nealust kokkulepet kohaldatakse meremeeste suhtes, kes t&ouml;&ouml;tavad kas eraisikule v&otilde;i avalik-&otilde;iguslikule isikule kuuluval merelaeval, mis on registrisse kantud m&otilde;ne liikmesriigi territooriumil ning tavap&auml;raselt tegeleb kaubandusliku meres&otilde;iduga; </eesti>
<inglise> (5) The purpose of this Directive is to apply the provisions of Directive 1999/63/EC which reflect the provisions of ILO Convention No 180, to any ship calling at a Community port, irrespective of the flag it flies in order to identify and remedy any situation which is manifestly hazardous for the safety or health of seafarers; however, Directive 1999/63/EC includes requirements which are not to be found in ILO Convention No 180 and which should not therefore be enforced on board ships not flying the flag of a Member State; </inglise>
<eesti> 5) k&auml;esoleva direktiivi eesm&auml;rk on kohaldada direktiivi 1999/63/E&Uuml; ILO konventsiooni nr 180 kajastavaid s&auml;tteid k&otilde;ikide &uuml;henduse sadamates peatuvate laevade suhtes, s&otilde;ltumata sellest, millise lipu all nad s&otilde;idavad, et tuvastada meremeestele ilmselgelt ohtlikud v&otilde;i nende tervist kahjustavad olukorrad ja neid parandada; direktiiv 1999/63/E&Uuml; sisaldab siiski ka n&otilde;udeid, mida ILO konventsioonis nr 180 ei leidu ja mida seep&auml;rast ei tohiks rakendada laevadel, mis ei s&otilde;ida &uuml;hegi liikmesriigi lipu all; </eesti>
<inglise> (6) Directive 1999/63/EC applies to seafarers on board every seagoing ship registered in the territory of a Member State; Member States should monitor compliance with all the provisions of the said Directive by ships registered in their territory; </inglise>
<eesti> 6) direktiivi 1999/63/E&Uuml; kohaldatakse liikmesriigi territooriumil registrisse kantud merelaevade pardal olevate meremeeste suhtes; liikmesriigid peaksid j&auml;lgima, et nende territooriumil registrisse kantud laevad j&auml;rgivad k&otilde;iki k&otilde;nealuse direktiivi s&auml;tteid; </eesti>
<inglise> (7) In order to protect safety and to avoid distortions of competition, Member States should be allowed to verify compliance with the relevant provisions of Directive 1999/63/EC by all sea-going vessels calling at their ports, irrespective of the State in which they are registered; </inglise>
<eesti> 7) turvalisuse kaitseks ja konkurentsi moonutamise v&auml;ltimiseks peaks liikmesriikidel olema lubatud kontrollida, et k&otilde;ik nende sadamates peatuvad merelaevad, s&otilde;ltumata sellest, millises liikmesriigis need registrisse on kantud, j&auml;rgivad direktiivi 1999/63/E&Uuml; asjakohaseid s&auml;tteid; </eesti>
<inglise> (8) In particular, ships flying the flag of a State which is not a party to ILO Convention No 180 or the Protocol to ILO Convention No 147 should not receive more favourable treatment than those flying the flag of a State which is a party to either the Convention or Protocol or to both of them; </inglise>
<eesti> 8) eelk&otilde;ige ei tohiks laevu, mis s&otilde;idavad ILO konventsiooniga nr 180 v&otilde;i ILO konventsiooni nr 147 protokolliga &uuml;hinemata riigi lipu all, kohelda soodsamalt kui laevu, mis s&otilde;idavad kas k&otilde;nealuse konventsiooni v&otilde;i protokolliga v&otilde;i nende m&otilde;lemaga &uuml;hinenud riigi lipu all; </eesti>
<inglise> (9) For the control of the effective enforcement of Directive 1999/63/EC, it is necessary that Member States carry out inspections on board ships, notably after having received a complaint by the master, a crew member, or any person or organisation with a legitimate interest in the safe operation of the ship, shipboard living and working conditions or the prevention of pollution; </inglise>
<eesti> 9) direktiivi 1999/63/E&Uuml; t&otilde;husa t&auml;itmise kontrollimiseks on vajalik, et liikmesriigid korraldavad laevadel kontrolle, eelk&otilde;ige siis, kui on saadud kaebus laeva kaptenilt, laevapere liikmelt v&otilde;i isikult v&otilde;i organisatsioonilt, kelle &otilde;igustatud huvides on laeva ohutu ekspluateerimine, selle elu- ja t&ouml;&ouml;tingimused v&otilde;i saaste &auml;rahoidmine; </eesti>
<inglise> (10) For the purposes of this Directive Member States, on their own initiative, may designate, as appropriate, Port State Control inspectors to carry out inspections on board vessels calling at Community ports; </inglise>
<eesti> 10) k&auml;esoleva direktiivi kohaldamisel v&otilde;ivad liikmesriigid vajaduse korral omal algatusel nimetada ametisse sadamariikide j&auml;relevalveinspektorid, kes korraldavad kontrolle &uuml;henduse sadamates peatuvatel laevadel; </eesti>
<inglise> (11) Evidence that a ship does not comply with the requirements of Directive 1999/63/EC may be obtained after verification of the shipboard working arrangements and seafarers' records of hours of work or hours of rest, or when the inspector has a reasonable belief that seafarers are excessively fatigued; </inglise>
<eesti> 11) t&otilde;endeid selle kohta, et laev ei j&auml;rgi direktiivi 1999/63/E&Uuml; n&otilde;udeid, v&otilde;ib saada p&auml;rast laeva t&ouml;&ouml;tingimuste ja meremeeste t&ouml;&ouml;- v&otilde;i puhkeaja registri kontrollimist v&otilde;i kui inspektoril on p&otilde;hjendatud alus arvata, et meremehed on &uuml;lev&auml;sinud; </eesti>
<inglise> (12) In order to rectify any conditions on board a ship which are clearly hazardous to safety or health, the competent authority of the Member State in whose port the ship has called may impose a prohibition on leaving the port until the deficiencies found have been rectified or the crew is sufficiently rested; </inglise>
<eesti> 12) laeval valitsevate ilmselgelt ohtlike v&otilde;i tervistkahjustavate tingimuste parandamiseks v&otilde;ib selle liikmesriigi p&auml;dev asutus, kelle sadamas laev peatub, keelata laeval sadamast lahkuda, kuni vead k&otilde;rvaldatakse v&otilde;i laevapere on piisavalt puhanud; </eesti>
<inglise> (13) Since Directive 1999/63/EC reflects the provisions of ILO Convention No 180, verification of compliance with the provisions of that Directive by ships registered in the territory of a third State can take place only when this Convention has entered into force, </inglise>
<eesti> 13) kuna direktiivis 1999/63/E&Uuml; kajastatakse ILO konventsiooni nr 180 s&auml;tteid, saab seda, kas kolmandas riigis registrisse kantud laevad k&otilde;nealuse direktiivi s&auml;tteid j&auml;rgivad, kontrollida alles p&auml;rast nimetatud konventsiooni j&otilde;ustumist, </eesti>
<inglise> HAVE ADOPTED THIS DIRECTIVE: </inglise>
<eesti> ON VASTU V&Otilde;TNUD K&Auml;ESOLEVA DIREKTIIVI. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 1 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 1 </eesti>
<inglise> Purpose and scope </inglise>
<eesti> Eesm&auml;rk ja reguleerimisala </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> The purpose of this Directive is to provide a mechanism for the verification and enforcement of compliance by ships calling at ports of Member States with Directive 1999/63/EC in order to improve maritime safety, working conditions and the health and safety of seafarers on board ships. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esoleva direktiivi eesm&auml;rk on kehtestada kord, mille alusel saab kontrollida, kas liikmesriikide sadamates peatuvad laevad j&auml;rgivad direktiivi 1999/63/E&Uuml;, et parandada meres&otilde;iduohutust, t&ouml;&ouml;tingimusi ja meremeeste tervist ja ohutust laevadel. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> Member States shall take appropriate measures to ensure that ships which are not registered in their territory or not flying their flag comply with clauses 1 to 12 of the Agreement annexed to Directive 1999/63/EC. </inglise>
<eesti> Liikmesriigid v&otilde;tavad asjakohased meetmed selle tagamiseks, et laevad, mis ei ole registrisse kantud nende territooriumil v&otilde;i mis ei s&otilde;ida nende lipu all, j&auml;rgivad direktiivile 1999/63/E&Uuml; lisatud kokkuleppe klausleid 1-12. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 2 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 2 </eesti>
<inglise> Definitions </inglise>
<eesti> M&otilde;isted </eesti>
<inglise> For the purposes of this Directive, </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolevas direktiivis kasutatakse j&auml;rgmisi m&otilde;isteid: </eesti>
<inglise> (a) "ship" means any seagoing vessel, whether publicly or privately owned, which is ordinarily engaged in commercial maritime operations. </inglise>
<eesti> a) laev - eraisikule v&otilde;i avalik-&otilde;iguslikule isikule kuuluv merelaev, mis tavap&auml;raselt tegeleb kaubandusliku meres&otilde;iduga. </eesti>
<inglise> Fishing vessels are not included in this definition, </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev m&auml;&auml;ratlus ei h&otilde;lma kalalaevu, </eesti>
<inglise> (b) "competent authority" means the authorities designated by the Member States to perform functions under this Directive, </inglise>
<eesti> b) p&auml;dev asutus - asutus, mille liikmesriik on m&auml;&auml;ranud k&auml;esoleva direktiivis s&auml;testatud &uuml;lesannete t&auml;itmiseks, </eesti>
<inglise> (c) "inspector" means a public-sector employee or other person, duly authorised by the competent authority of a Member State to inspect the working conditions on board, and responsible to that competent authority, </inglise>
<eesti> c) inspektor - avalik teenistuja v&otilde;i isik, kelle liikmesriigi p&auml;dev asutus on n&otilde;uetekohaselt volitanud kontrollima laeval valitsevaid t&ouml;&ouml;tingimusi ja kes allub k&otilde;nealusele p&auml;devale asutusele, </eesti>
<inglise> (d) "complaint" means any information or report submitted by a member of the crew, a professional body, an association, a trade union or, generally, any person with an interest in the safety of the ship, including an interest in safety or health hazards to its crew. </inglise>
<eesti> d) kaebus - teave v&otilde;i aruanne, mille esitab laevapere liige, kutseorganisatsioon, &uuml;hendus, ameti&uuml;hing v&otilde;i isik, kes on huvitatud laeva ohutusest, sealhulgas laevapere ohutusest ja terviseriskidest. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 3 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 3 </eesti>
<inglise> Preparation of reports </inglise>
<eesti> Aruannete koostamine </eesti>
<inglise> Without prejudice to Article 1 (2), if a Member State in whose port a ship calls voluntarily in the normal course of its business or for operational reasons receives a complaint which it does not consider manifestly unfounded or obtains evidence that the ship does not conform to the standards referred to in Directive 1999/63/EC, it shall prepare a report addressed to the government of the country in which the ship is registered and, when an inspection carried out pursuant to Article 4 provides relevant evidence, the Member State shall take the measures necessary to ensure that any conditions on board which are clearly hazardous to the safety or the health of the crew are rectified. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui liikmesriik, kelle sadamas laev vabatahtlikult tavap&auml;rastel kaubanduslikel eesm&auml;rkidel v&otilde;i funktsionaalsetel p&otilde;hjustel peatub, on saanud kaebuse, mida ta ei loe selgelt alusetuks, v&otilde;i t&otilde;endeid, et laev ei vasta direktiivis 1999/63/EM&Uuml; nimetatud normidele, koostab ta aruande, mille adresseerib selle riigi valitsusele, kelle territooriumil laev registrisse on kantud, ja kui artikli 4 alusel korraldatud kontrolli tulemusel saadakse asjakohased t&otilde;endid, v&otilde;tab liikmesriik meetmed, mis on vajalikud laeval valitsevate laevaperele ilmselgelt ohtlike v&otilde;i tervist kahjustavate tingimuste parandamise tagamiseks, ilma et see piiraks artikli 1 l&otilde;ike 2 kohaldamist. </eesti>
<inglise> The identity of the person lodging the report or the complaint must not be revealed to the master or the owner of the ship concerned. </inglise>
<eesti> Aruande v&otilde;i kaebuse esitanud isikut ei v&otilde;i asjaomase laeva kaptenile v&otilde;i omanikule avaldada. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 4 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 4 </eesti>
<inglise> Inspection and more detailed inspection </inglise>
<eesti> Kontroll ja &uuml;ksikasjalik kontroll </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> When carrying out an inspection, in order to obtain evidence that a ship does not conform to the requirements of Directive 1999/63/EC, the inspector shall determine whether: </inglise>
<eesti> Kui kontrolli eesm&auml;rk on saada t&otilde;endeid selle kohta, et laev ei vasta direktiivi 1999/63/E&Uuml; n&otilde;uetele, kontrollib inspektor, kas: </eesti>
<inglise> - a table with the shipboard working arrangements has been established in the working language or languages of the ship and in English according to the model format reproduced in Annex I, or in an alternative equivalent format, and is posted on board in an easily accessible place; </inglise>
<eesti> - laeval on selle t&ouml;&ouml;korraldust kajastav tabel, mis on koostatud vastavalt I lisas esitatud n&auml;idisvormile v&otilde;i m&otilde;nes muus samalaadses vormis nii laeva t&ouml;&ouml;keeltes kui ka inglise keeles ja kinnitatud kergesti juurdep&auml;&auml;setavasse paika; </eesti>
<inglise> - seafarers' records of hours of work or hours of rest have been established in the working language or languages of the ship and in English according to the model format reproduced in Annex II, or in an alternative equivalent format, and are kept on board and there is proof that the records have been endorsed by the competent authority of the State where the ship is registered. </inglise>
<eesti> - meremeeste t&ouml;&ouml;- v&otilde;i puhkeaja register on koostatud vastavalt II lisas esitatud n&auml;idisvormile v&otilde;i m&otilde;nes muus samalaadses vormis nii laeva t&ouml;&ouml;keeltes kui ka inglise keeles ja seda hoitakse laeva pardal ning kas on t&otilde;endeid, et registri on kinnitanud selle riigi p&auml;dev asutus, kelle territooriumil laev on registrisse kantud. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> If a complaint has been received or the inspector from his own observations on board believes that the seafarers may be unduly fatigued, the inspector shall conduct a more detailed inspection, pursuant to paragraph 1, to determine whether the working hours or rest periods recorded conform to the standards laid down in Directive 1999/63/EC and that they have been duly observed, taking into account other records relating to the operation of the ship. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui on saabunud kaebus v&otilde;i inspektor usub pardal tehtud t&auml;helepanekute p&otilde;hjal, et meremehed v&otilde;ivad olla &uuml;lev&auml;sinud, korraldab inspektor l&otilde;ike 1 kohaselt &uuml;ksikasjalikuma kontrolli, et kontrollida, kas kirjapandud t&ouml;&ouml;- v&otilde;i puhkeaeg vastab direktiiviga 1999/63/E&Uuml; etten&auml;htud normidele ja kas neid norme on n&otilde;uetekohaselt j&auml;rgitud, v&otilde;ttes arvesse muid laeva ekspluateerimisega seotud m&auml;rkmeid. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 5 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 5 </eesti>
<inglise> The rectification of deficiencies </inglise>
<eesti> Vigade k&otilde;rvaldamine </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> If the inspection or the more detailed inspection reveals that the ship does not conform to the requirements of Directive 1999/63/EC, the Member State shall take the measures necessary to ensure that any conditions on board which are clearly hazardous to the safety or health of seafarers are rectified. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui kontrolli v&otilde;i &uuml;ksikasjaliku kontrolli tagaj&auml;rjel ilmneb, et laev ei vasta direktiivi 1999/63/E&Uuml; n&otilde;uetele, v&otilde;tavad liikmesriigid meetmed, mis on vajalikud laeval valitsevate meremeestele ilmselgelt ohtlike v&otilde;i nende tervist kahjustavate tingimuste parandamise tagamiseks. </eesti>
<inglise> Such measures may include a prohibition on leaving the port until deficiencies have been rectified or the seafarers have been sufficiently rested. </inglise>
<eesti> Nende meetmete hulka v&otilde;ib kuuluda keeld lahkuda sadamast, kuni vead k&otilde;rvaldatakse v&otilde;i meremehed on piisavalt puhanud. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> If there is clear evidence that watchkeeping personnel for the first watch or subsequent relieving watches are unduly fatigued, the Member State shall ensure that the ship shall not leave port until the deficiencies found have been rectified or the seafarers in question have been sufficiently rested. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui on selgeid t&otilde;endeid, et esimese vahi v&otilde;i sellele j&auml;rgnevate vahtide vahimehed on &uuml;lev&auml;sinud, kindlustab liikmesriik, et laev ei lahku sadamast enne, kui leitud vead k&otilde;rvaldatakse v&otilde;i asjaomased meremehed on piisavalt puhanud. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 6 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 6 </eesti>
<inglise> Follow-up procedures </inglise>
<eesti> Edaspidised menetlused </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> In the event that a ship is prohibited from leaving the port pursuant to Article 5, the competent authority of the Member State shall inform the master, the owner or operator, the administration of the flag State or the State where the ship is registered or the Consul, or in his absence the nearest diplomatic representative of the State, of the results of the inspections referred to in Article 4, of any decisions taken by the inspector and of corrective actions required, if necessary. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui laeval on artikli 5 kohaselt keelatud sadamast lahkuda, teatab liikmesriigi p&auml;dev asutus laeva kaptenile, omanikule v&otilde;i kasutajale, lipuriigi v&otilde;i riigi, mille territooriumil laev registrisse on kantud, administratsioonile v&otilde;i konsulile v&otilde;i tema puudumise korral l&auml;himale k&otilde;nealuse riigi diplomaatilisele esindajale artiklis 4 nimetatud kontrollide tulemustest, inspektori tehtud otsustest ja vajaduse korral n&otilde;utavatest korrektiivmeetmetest. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> When carrying out an inspection under this Directive, all possible efforts should be made to avoid a ship being unduly delayed. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esoleva direktiivi kohast kontrolli tehes tuleks igal v&otilde;imalusel v&auml;ltida laeva p&otilde;hjendamatut kinnipidamist. </eesti>
<inglise> If a ship is unduly delayed, the owner or operator shall be entitled to compensation for any loss or damage suffered. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui laeva on p&otilde;hjendamatult kinni peetud, on selle omanikul v&otilde;i kasutajal &otilde;igus h&uuml;vitisele kogu kahjumi v&otilde;i kahjude eest. </eesti>
<inglise> In any instance of alleged undue delay, the burden of proof shall lie with the owner or operator of the ship. </inglise>
<eesti> V&auml;idetava p&otilde;hjendamatu kinnipidamise puhul on t&otilde;endamiskohustus laeva omanikul v&otilde;i kasutajal. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 7 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 7 </eesti>
<inglise> Right of appeal </inglise>
<eesti> Kaebuse esitamise &otilde;igus </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> The owner or the operator of the ship or his representative in the Member State shall have a right of appeal against a detention decision taken by the competent authority. </inglise>
<eesti> Laeva omanikul v&otilde;i kasutajal v&otilde;i tema esindajal liikmesriigis on &otilde;igus esitada p&auml;deva asutuse tehtud kinnipidamisotsuse kohta kaebus. </eesti>
<inglise> An appeal shall not cause the detention to be suspended. </inglise>
<eesti> Kaebuse esitamine ei l&uuml;kka kinnipidamist edasi. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> Member States shall establish and maintain appropriate procedures for this purpose in accordance with their national legislation. </inglise>
<eesti> Selleks kehtestavad ja s&auml;ilitavad liikmesriigid vastavalt oma siseriiklikele &otilde;igusaktidele asjakohase korra. </eesti>
<inglise> 3. </inglise>
<eesti> 3. </eesti>
<inglise> The competent authority shall properly inform the master of a ship referred to in paragraph 1 of the right of appeal. </inglise>
<eesti> P&auml;dev asutus teatab l&otilde;ikes 1 nimetatud laeva omanikule n&otilde;uetekohaselt kaebuse esitamise &otilde;igusest. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 8 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 8 </eesti>
<inglise> Administrative cooperation </inglise>
<eesti> Halduskoost&ouml;&ouml; </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> Member States shall take the necessary steps to provide, in conditions compatible with those laid down in Article 14 of Directive 95/21/EC of 19 June 1995 concerning the enforcement, in respect of shipping using Community ports and sailing in the waters under the jurisdiction of the Member States, of international standards for ship safety, pollution prevention and shipboard living and working conditions (port State control) (5), for cooperation between their relevant authorities and the relevant competent authorities of other Member States to ensure the effective application of this Directive and shall notify the Commission of the provision made. </inglise>
<eesti> Liikmesriigid v&otilde;tavad vastavalt 19. juuni 1995. aasta direktiivi 95/21/E&Uuml; (laevaohutust, saaste v&auml;ltimist ning elu- ja t&ouml;&ouml;tingimusi laevadel k&auml;sitlevate rahvusvaheliste n&otilde;uete rakendamise kohta &uuml;henduse sadamaid kasutavate ja liikmesriikide jurisdiktsiooni all olevates vetes s&otilde;itvate laevade suhtes (sadamariikide j&auml;relevalve)) (5) artiklis 14 s&auml;testatud tingimustele vajalikud abin&otilde;ud nende asjaomaste asutuste ja teiste liikmesriikide asjakohaste p&auml;devate asutuste vaheliseks koost&ouml;&ouml;ks, et tagada k&auml;esoleva direktiivi tulemuslik kohaldamine, ja teatavad sellest komisjonile. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> Information on the measures taken pursuant to Articles 4 and 5 shall be published in accordance with procedures such as those set out in the first paragraph of Article 15 of Directive 95/21/EC. </inglise>
<eesti> Teave artiklite 4 ja 5 kohaselt v&otilde;etud meetmete kohta avaldatakse direktiivi 95/21/E&Uuml; artikli 15 esimeses l&otilde;igus s&auml;testatud korras. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 9 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 9 </eesti>
<inglise> "No more favourable" treatment clause </inglise>
<eesti> Sooduskohtlemist keelav klausel </eesti>
<inglise> When inspecting a ship registered in the territory of or flying the flag of a State which has not signed ILO Convention No 180 or the Protocol to ILO Convention No 147, Member States shall, once the Convention and the Protocol are in force, ensure that the treatment given to such ships and their crew is no more favourable than that given to a ship flying the flag of a State which is a party to either ILO Convention No 180 or the Protocol to ILO Convention No 147 or both of them. </inglise>
<eesti> Kontrollides laevu, mis on registrisse kantud ILO konventsiooniga nr 180 v&otilde;i ILO konventsiooni nr 147 protokolliga &uuml;hinemata riigis v&otilde;i mis s&otilde;idavad sellise riigi lipu all, tagavad liikmesriigid alates k&otilde;nealuse konventsiooni ja protokolli j&otilde;ustumisest, et selliseid laevu ja nende laevaperet ei kohelda soodsamalt kui laevu, mis s&otilde;idavad kas ILO konventsiooniga nr 180 v&otilde;i ILO konventsiooni nr 147 protokolliga v&otilde;i nende m&otilde;lemaga &uuml;hinenud riigi lipu all. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 10 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 10 </eesti>
<inglise> Final provisions </inglise>
<eesti> L&otilde;pps&auml;tted </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> Member States shall bring into force the laws, regulations and administrative provisions necessary to comply with this Directive not later than 30 June 2002. </inglise>
